Can you share some code? Ah i see know, F7 only keeps the current and previous page. So if the navigation is `Home > About > Services > Contact` then Contact & Services are kept in DOM.

To avoid reapplying event listeners F7 doesn't trigger `page:init` everytime the page becomes visible however as going back means About is now the previous page so F7 fetches it and runs `page:init` on it ensuring it's ready should the user go back again

TL;DR: this is a feature, not a bug  This PR has fundamental issue. As such rerendering will break all components initialized by "page:init" and won't detach all assigned events and destroy initialized components, so potentially can lead to memory leaks as well. So it is good for something simple but won't work and break things in case you have something more complex. Also, it won't work on iOS theme if you have some dynamic data in navbar because it is rendered outside of page. So to make it work correctly the page should be destroyed correctly then rerendered and added/replaced by new one and re-initialized. To make it work, it is possible to use view router's method, something like:
```js
function renderPage(data) {
    var tpl = Template7.cache[this.url];
    var newData = data || this.data || {};

    view.router.load({
        template: tpl,
        reload: true,
        reloadPrevious: $(this.container).hasClass('page-on-left'),
        context: newData
    });
}  @J05HI you'll see I've assigned @nolimits4web (he get's the final say) but he's quite busy and probably hasn't had time to look at it yet. @J05HI we do care but we aren't paid to maintain F7 so we can only deal with issues / PR's in our free time. @J05HI while this PR is fixing the issue, in same time it provides different look and feel, which is not so "material". Need to think about how to fix it and keep the same look and behavior  you probably need to reinitialize the search bar Yes, as @ZanderBrown stated, searchbar should be reinitialized as well. But it is not recommended to change it on the fly, it is better to reload the page and init app again with rtl styles  How many editors respect `.editorconfig`? Thanks!  @macdonst folks agree :)  That works. @Tarekajaj could you tidy the indentation please? Thanks  Well, for some reason i can not replicate it and it works fine for me. Can anyone confirm there is such issue? 
