 Here is a small sneak peek of F7 Vue plugin and things I already successfully achieved:
- Almost all F7 components are wrapped into Vue components which saves a lot of markup and also allows to differentiate some iOS/Material difference in layout automatically within components
- And I finally implemented a bit different router that allows to load Vue components as pages. This was the hardest task. For this I added to native F7 router ability to pass page HTMElelement which is added to Dom and rendered by Vue and F7's router just do the animation stuff with further required pages callbacks and pages initialization. I believe same logic can be reused in React implementation 
- I also added a fix to F7 that allows to use same page structure with navbar inside of page, and it automatically moves it out of page and put to correct place if you use dynamicNavbar
