 preventClicks works, but i'll try to explain it more detailed. Slider prevents click event during swipes and its click event handler is set on "slider-container". This is made to prevent clicks on default HTML elements like <a> and disable F7's clicks handler when required.

You have to understand that if you add your custom click handler on something that is inside of slider, then slider's preventClicks will not intercept it, because your click handler is deeper in DOM than slider's one.
So if you want to add your custom handler that should be also prevented by Slider you may add it on element that is parent to slider-container, for example, using live event:

```
$$(document).on('click', '.slider-container .something', function (){...})
```
