Here is more info on how linking works
When you click any link (&lt;a&gt;) here is what happens:
1) First of all F7 checks does it have additional "external" class. If link has this class, then F7 doesn't do anything with this link, and it works like usual browser link, so it just reloads browser window to new URL if you don't have custom event handlers on this link.
2) Otherwise, if link's href is not '#' it will try to do Ajax request and load new page with transition in View.
3) Now the question is in which View new page should be loaded. Here, F7 search first link's parent div class="view". And if this found view was initialized with <code>app.addView()</code> page will be loaded here
4) Otherwise if there is no any parent View or there is no parent initialized View, F7 look at link's <code>data-view</code> attribute which could point on another view. And if there is no this attribute new page will be loaded to main view
