  There is actually exist more beautiful solution in Less, we can show rules depending on arguments, on example of align-items:

```
.align-items(@ai) when (@ai = flex-start) {
    -webkit-box-align: start;
    -moz-box-align: start;
    -ms-flex-align: start;
    -webkit-align-items: flex-start;
    align-items: flex-start;
}
.align-items(@ai) when (@ai = flex-end) {
    -webkit-box-align: end;
    -moz-box-align: end;
    -ms-flex-align: end;
    -webkit-align-items: flex-end;
    align-items: flex-end;
}
.align-items(@ai) when not (@ai = flex-start) and not (@ai = flex-end) {
    -webkit-box-align: @ai;
    -moz-box-align: @ai;
    -ms-flex-align: @ai;
    -webkit-align-items: @ai;
    align-items: @ai;
}
